<br>Source: The Circle City
<br>Common: Körvá
<br>Elven: Dynas Gyll
<br>Dwarven: 
<br>Orcish: 
<br><br>
<br>Predominately <a data-href="Human" href="https://karlsayle.github.io/Human" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener">Human</a> but other non-magical races visit often for trade
<br><br>
<br>Körvá gets its name from its impressive circular outer wall - directly translating to 'The Circle City'
<br>The Folyó (river) Kör winds its way through the city from the North East to the Southern border
<br>Even though magic was forbidden and looked down upon as cheap tricks and a way of cheating a good day's work, the people of Körvá still knew the value of knowledge, and the value of understanding the magical races (‘Know your foe’) and so had a vast resource of books and scripture curated by their most respected sages over the period of the city's history.&nbsp;
<br>Despite the people's outlook on magic, the restricted area has a sizeable collection of books on the arcane and the occult which is restricted to all but the highest ranking military officials, sages, politicians and members of the royal family.
<br>The people of Körvá pride themselves on being a democratic and fair society where men and women are seen as equals.
<br>Körvá has a strong military force that protects their people and interests both domestically and abroad. It is governed primarily by parliament but also answers to the royal family as has been the city's tradition for centuries.
<br>The people have a strong work ethic - a hard day's work is a hard day's work regardless of whether you are a knight or a farmer, they are all equally respected.&nbsp;
]]></description><link>https://karlsayle.github.io/places/steadings/körvá.html</link><guid isPermaLink="false">Places/Steadings/Körvá.md</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Karl Sayle]]></dc:creator><pubDate>Mon, 26 Feb 2024 22:09:10 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[Welcome]]></title><description><![CDATA[ 
 <br><br>Use either the navigation on the left or the Interactive Graph on the right to find  your way around]]></description><link>https://karlsayle.github.io/index.html</link><guid isPermaLink="false">Index.md</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Karl Sayle]]></dc:creator><pubDate>Mon, 26 Feb 2024 22:08:28 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[Race/Class]]></title><description><![CDATA[<a class="tag" href="https://karlsayle.github.io/?query=tag:year_1330" style="background-color: rgb(4, 108, 116); color: white; font-weight: 700; border: none; border-radius: 1em; padding: 0.2em 0.5em;">#year_1330</a> 
 <br><br><a data-href="Human" href="https://karlsayle.github.io/Human" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener">Human</a> <a data-href="Warlock" href="https://karlsayle.github.io/Warlock" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener">Warlock</a><br><br><a data-tooltip-position="top" aria-label="Körvá" data-href="Körvá" href="https://karlsayle.github.io/places/steadings/körvá.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener">Körvá</a><br><br><a data-href="Vellamo" href="https://karlsayle.github.io/characters/families/vellamo.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener">Vellamo</a><br><br>
<br>The youngest of three children, Ilkka has a brother and a sister with his brother being the eldest. Both his brother and sister were trained from a young age to be excellent fighters, well versed in both combat and diplomacy.
<br>Ilkka did not take well to combat training, certainly not to the level of his brother and sister preferring the book to the sword.
<br>Ilkka’s uncle is king of <a data-href="Korva" href="https://karlsayle.github.io/Korva" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener">Korva</a>.
<br>Coming from a royal background, Ilkka had a privileged upbringing. However, his people shunned magic of all kinds favouring strength, hard work and traditional ways over the arcane.
<br>With Ilkka being a member of the royal family, albeit a fairly minor royal, he was privileged enough to be allowed access to the restricted areas of the <a data-tooltip-position="top" aria-label="Körvá" data-href="Körvá" href="https://karlsayle.github.io/places/steadings/körvá.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener">city</a> library.
<br><br>
<br>Ilkka has been a keen student all of his life with a keen interest in the history of the wider world and secretly, magic. He stumbled upon numerous legends of powerful, oftentimes evil, wizards and unfathomable creatures that rivalled the power of the gods. This was how he found <a data-href="The Great Old One" href="https://karlsayle.github.io/characters/npcs/the-great-old-one.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener">The Great Old One</a> - now his patron after unknowingly making a pact as a young adolescent. This was the birth of Ilkka <a data-href="Vellamo" href="https://karlsayle.github.io/characters/families/vellamo.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener">Vellamo</a>, the <a data-href="Warlock" href="https://karlsayle.github.io/Warlock" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener">Warlock</a>.
<br>Ilkka’s transition to becoming a <a data-href="Warlock" href="https://karlsayle.github.io/Warlock" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener">Warlock</a> was not an overnight event but a slow transition where his powers presented themselves often by accident. Through his fervent studying, he learned of his inadvertent pact and his powers. Although, his knowledge of <a data-href="The Great Old One" href="https://karlsayle.github.io/characters/npcs/the-great-old-one.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener">The Great Old One</a> was very small and spurred an obsession to find out more of this unknown being. The more he learned, the more his powers grew. This was not well received by his family or his people. Whilst his <a data-tooltip-position="top" aria-label="Vellamo, Vilmos" data-href="Vellamo, Vilmos" href="https://karlsayle.github.io/characters/npcs/vellamo,-vilmos.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener">father</a> tried to quash any calls for him to be exiled from the city, a <a data-tooltip-position="top" aria-label="The Banishment of Géna Vellamo" data-href="The Banishment of Géna Vellamo" href="https://karlsayle.github.io/events/the-banishment-of-géna-vellamo.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener">terrible accident</a> resulted in Ilkka banishing his <a data-tooltip-position="top" aria-label="Vellamo, Géna" data-href="Vellamo, Géna" href="https://karlsayle.github.io/characters/npcs/vellamo,-géna.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener">mother</a> to another, unknown realm. This was the last straw, Ilkka was immediately exiled from the <a data-tooltip-position="top" aria-label="Körvá" data-href="Körvá" href="https://karlsayle.github.io/places/steadings/körvá.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener">city</a> and disowned by his family. He was only 15 years of age. The guilt and sadness that followed plunged Ilkka into years of depression pushing him to the brink of starvation and worse.
<br>After being taken in by a <a data-href="librarian" href="https://karlsayle.github.io/characters/npcs/librarian.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener">librarian</a> in <a data-tooltip-position="top" aria-label="Kőris" data-href="Kőris" href="https://karlsayle.github.io/places/steadings/kőris.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener">Kőris</a> a number of years later ( <a href="https://karlsayle.github.io?query=tag:year_1330" class="tag" target="_blank" rel="noopener">#year_1330</a> ), he rediscovered his love of books and for research. This reignited his desire to discover more about <a data-href="The Great Old One" href="https://karlsayle.github.io/characters/npcs/the-great-old-one.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener">The Great Old One</a> and through him, find his mother.
<br>Finding his mother and details of his patron, <a data-href="The Great Old One" href="https://karlsayle.github.io/characters/npcs/the-great-old-one.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener">The Great Old One</a>, have been his primary driving force behind becoming an adventurer at the young age of 21.&nbsp;
<br><br>
<br><a data-href="The Great Old One" href="https://karlsayle.github.io/characters/npcs/the-great-old-one.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener">The Great Old One</a>
<br>All that is known of Ilkka’s patron is that he/she is some form of unfathomable beast with an understanding of the world and universe rivalled by none.
<br>Ilkkas relationship with his patron borders on an obsession; the more he discovers about his patron, the more his desire grows to ascend to his/her level of knowledge and understanding of the universe. Ilkka believes that his devotion to his patron will lead him to find a way to bring his mother back.
<br>Ilkka is unaware of what his patron expects in return for the powers granted to him - so far, his dedication appears to be enough.
<br>Ilkka receives messages from his patron in the most random of places; books, written in the clouds and in the bark of a tree. These messages are only visible to Ilkka. However, his patron mostly communicates via Ilkkas dreams. These dreams take the form of uncomfortable, almost nightmarish dreams often etched with the guilt of his past.
]]></description><link>https://karlsayle.github.io/characters/pcs/vellamo,-ilkka.html</link><guid isPermaLink="false">Characters/PCs/Vellamo, Ilkka.md</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Karl Sayle]]></dc:creator><pubDate>Mon, 26 Feb 2024 21:24:02 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[Who]]></title><description><![CDATA[<a class="tag" href="https://karlsayle.github.io/?query=tag:year_1328" style="background-color: rgb(4, 108, 116); color: white; font-weight: 700; border: none; border-radius: 1em; padding: 0.2em 0.5em;">#year_1328</a> 
 <br><a href="https://karlsayle.github.io?query=tag:year_1328" class="tag" target="_blank" rel="noopener">#year_1328</a><br><br>
<br><a data-href="Vellamo, Géna" href="https://karlsayle.github.io/characters/npcs/vellamo,-géna.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener">Vellamo, Géna</a>
<br><a data-href="Vellamo, Ilkka" href="https://karlsayle.github.io/characters/pcs/vellamo,-ilkka.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener">Vellamo, Ilkka</a>
<br><br>
<br>Whilst still coming to terms and trying to understand his growing powers, it was thought that (by the people of <a data-href="Körvá" href="https://karlsayle.github.io/places/steadings/körvá.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener">Körvá</a>), <a data-tooltip-position="top" aria-label="Vellamo, Ilkka" data-href="Vellamo, Ilkka" href="https://karlsayle.github.io/characters/pcs/vellamo,-ilkka.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener">Ilkka</a> accidentally killed his <a data-tooltip-position="top" aria-label="Vellamo, Géna" data-href="Vellamo, Géna" href="https://karlsayle.github.io/characters/npcs/vellamo,-géna.html" class="internal-link" target="_self" rel="noopener">mother</a> during a heated argument.
<br>However, Ilkka maintains that he did not kill her, but instead transported her to a place unknown. An unknown realm perhaps?
<br><br>13 Március 1328<br><br>Unknown]]></description><link>https://karlsayle.github.io/events/the-banishment-of-géna-vellamo.html</link><guid isPermaLink="false">Events/The Banishment of Géna Vellamo.md</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Karl Sayle]]></dc:creator><pubDate>Mon, 26 Feb 2024 21:22:35 GMT</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[Who]]></title><description><![CDATA[<a class="tag" href="https://karlsayle.github.io/?query=tag:year_578" style="background-color: rgb(4, 108, 116); color: white; font-weight: 700; border: none; border-radius: 1em; padding: 0.2em 0.5em;">#year_578</a> 
